# Python Conventions

- Follow PEP 8, use type hints on function signatures
- Docstrings for public APIs (Google style)
- snake_case for functions/variables, PascalCase for classes, UPPER_SNAKE for constants
- Proper exception handling with specific exception types
- Context managers for resources (files, connections)
- Use `pytest` for testing, naming: `test_[function]_[scenario]_[expected]`
- Async/await for I/O operations where appropriate
- No `eval()` or dynamic code execution
- Parameterized queries only (no SQL string concatenation)
